{"cursor":"4458","size":14,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"The 'Perkin Medal' is an award given annually by the American section of the\nSociety of Chemical Industry to a scientist residing in America for an\n\"innovation in applied chemistry resulting in outstanding commercial\ndevelopment.\" It is considered the highest honor given in the US industrial\nchemical industry.\n\nThe Perkin Medal was first granted in 1906 to commemorate the 50th anniversary\nof the discovery of mauveine, the world's first synthetic aniline dye, by Sir\nWilliam Henry Perkin, an English chemist. The award was given to Sir William on\nthe occasion of his famous visit to the United States in the year before he\ndied. It was next given in 1908 and has been given every year since then.\n","linknr":195,"url":"Perkin_Medal","recorded":1363124242,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Perkin_Medal&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Perkin_Medal&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-head","#p-search","/wiki/United_States","/wiki/Society_of_Chemical_Industry","/wiki/Mauveine","/wiki/Chemical_synthesis","/wiki/Aniline","/wiki/Dye","/wiki/Sir_William_Henry_Perkin","/wiki/England","/w/index.php?title=Perkin_Medal&action=edit&section=1","/wiki/